<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="274" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,546,897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,691,717]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Remarks.</emphasis>
First records for 
<collectingCountry box="[513,611,691,717]" name="Hungary" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Hungary</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[667,772,691,717]" name="Romania" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Romania</collectingCountry>
. This species is known from several countries of the Western Palaearctic region; among them 
<collectingCountry box="[559,657,727,753]" name="Hungary" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Hungary</collectingCountry>
is also listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yu, D. S. &amp; van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K." box="[845,1025,727,753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274" refId="ref7112" refString="Yu, D. S., van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K. (2016) Taxapad 2016, Ichneumonoidea 2015. Nepean, Ontario. Database on flash-drive. Available from: http: // www. taxapad. com" type="url" year="2016">
Yu 
<emphasis box="[884,934,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, citing 
<bibRefCitation author="Chyzer, K." box="[1109,1275,727,753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274" pagination="206 - 209" refId="ref5807" refString="Chyzer, K. (1901) Zemplen megye Hymenopterai. II. (Die Hymenopteren des Komitates Zemplen. II.) Rovartani Lapok, 8, 206 - 209." type="journal article" year="1901">Chyzer (1901)</bibRefCitation>
. However, the locality given in 
<bibRefCitation author="Chyzer, K." box="[344,507,763,789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274" pagination="206 - 209" refId="ref5807" refString="Chyzer, K. (1901) Zemplen megye Hymenopterai. II. (Die Hymenopteren des Komitates Zemplen. II.) Rovartani Lapok, 8, 206 - 209." type="journal article" year="1901">Chyzer (1901)</bibRefCitation>
is Oroszruszka, which is actually a former Hungarian name of Stakčín, 
<collectingCountry box="[1330,1432,763,789]" name="Slovakia" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Slovakia</collectingCountry>
; therefore, this record refers to 
<collectingCountry box="[492,593,799,825]" name="Slovakia" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Slovakia</collectingCountry>
, not to 
<collectingCountry box="[675,775,799,825]" name="Hungary" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Hungary</collectingCountry>
. Hence, the record given above is to be considered the first report from 
<collectingCountry box="[288,388,835,861]" name="Hungary" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Hungary</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Chyzer, K." box="[399,566,835,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274" pagination="206 - 209" refId="ref5807" refString="Chyzer, K. (1901) Zemplen megye Hymenopterai. II. (Die Hymenopteren des Komitates Zemplen. II.) Rovartani Lapok, 8, 206 - 209." type="journal article" year="1901">Chyzer (1901)</bibRefCitation>
’s record should not be interpreted as the first Slovakian report of the species, since the referred voucher specimen was not found in HNHM and its identification is impossible to validate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
